      "value": "<p>Your companion is a fire elemental, such as a cinder rat or lava otter.</p>\n<p><strong>Access</strong> You are a member of the flame order SoM .</p>\n<p><strong>Size</strong> Small</p>\n<p><strong>Melee</strong> <span class=\"pf2-icon\">1</span> tendril (agile, finesse), <strong>Damage</strong> 1d6 fire</p>\n<p><strong>Str</strong> +2, <strong>Dex</strong> +2, <strong>Con</strong> +1, <strong>Int</strong> â€“4, <strong>Wis</strong> +1, <strong>Cha</strong> +0</p>\n<p><strong>Hit Points</strong> 4</p>\n<p><strong>Skill</strong> Intimidation</p>\n<p><strong>Senses</strong> darkvision</p>\n<p><strong>Speed</strong> 25 feet</p>\n<p><strong>Special</strong> Immunities fire, Weaknesses cold and water (equal to the fire elemental's level)</p>\n<p><strong>Support Benefit</strong> Your fire elemental burns your foes and sets them on fire. Until the start of your next turn, your Strikes that damage a creature in your fire elemental's reach also deal @Damage[1d6[persistent,fire]] damage. If your fire elemental is nimble or savage, the persistent fire damage increases to [[/r 2d6]].</p>\n<p><strong>Advanced Maneuver</strong> @UUID[Compendium.pf2e-animal-companions.AC-Advanced-Maneuvers.Item.LCilgiiIZp408R3k]{Flamethrower}</p>"
